 We'll learn how to keep many values together using lists, and how to process those values automatically using for loops to go through every item one at a time, while loops to repeat until a condition flips, and zip to pair items from two lists side by side. We'll also learn when each kind of loop is the right choice. We'll put those ideas together into a small project: a Spotify Playlist Ranker that takes a stream of songs and play counts, drops the low performers, and shows the rest as a ranked playlist.